{"TopicId":177639,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"Visiting the DRAO","CreatedByName":"55delta","CreatedById":101735,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-18T05:32:38Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"55delta","CreatedById":101735,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-18T05:32:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLast week I went and visited the Dominion Radio Astrophysical Observatory in British Columbia, Canada. There are a few radio telescopes there, the newest one being CHIME (Canadian Hydrogen Intensity Mapping Experiment). You could spend two or three hours there, more if you visit on a day with the guided tour.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone else been there?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-19T02:13:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo pictures?\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:mad:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_angry.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:mad:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mad Rocket Scientist","CreatedById":139256,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-19T05:13:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI haven\u0027t been there, but I have been to the Hawaii observatory. It doesn\u0027t really have a tour, although it does have a visitor center at lower altitude, which hosts night time star gazing parties with telescopes. I visited in the day, so I just looked through a solar telescope.\u00A0And I have pictures \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/27914-vanamonde/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002227914\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/27914-vanamonde/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Vanamonde\u003C/a\u003E. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EIt\u0027s amazing how close sea level is to high enough that you feel short of breath.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022rpqJsX7.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/rpqJsX7.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EThe observatories have signs saying to be careful of falling ice from the domes rotating, luckily it was pretty pleasant the day I was there:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ONxDb3e.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/ONxDb3e.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EYou could walk right up to and around the observatories. The ground\u00A0was completely barren at this altitude.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022AhoZt79.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/AhoZt79.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EThis was near the middle of summer in the northern hemisphere, so there was almost no shadow at noon.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022WiFw57X.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/WiFw57X.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EThere was also a volcano erupting. (sorry for the out of focus photo)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022IcdVmuA.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/IcdVmuA.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}